> There was a glance from WHEELIE, "I do not know this MAGMATRON, and I do
> not care if he is strong.  Let someone else deal with him as they may, I do not
> care this day.  He has not done anything against me, and my friends are
> beyond his grip I can see.  I do not care for this fight, for there will be
> another one in the coming night."
>
> WHEELIE glanced up and over at GRIMLOCk, "And really, TERRORCONS,
> working for someone else seems so begones.  I really wonder why this day,
> you're just general thugs for someone else anyway.  Why not do your own thing
> as you may?"

<NEW>

HUN-GRR smiled, his grin wide and toothy. "Oh yes, we work for someone
else now, we work for ourselves."

There were grunts and cackles from the other TERRORCONS.

"but imagine my surprise when Backstop here asked for our help in
capturing the Dinobots." HUN-GRR said as he looked at DINOBOT.

GRIMLOCK looked at BACKSTOP and then at HUN-GRR and then at WHEELIE,
"You mean you wanted to catch Grimlock?" The DINOBOT looked to be
hurt, and that hurt shifting over to anger.

"No . .  not exactly . .  Grimlock!' BACKSTOP stammered as he spoke,
"We had to slow you down so we could cure you of Magmatron's
influence."

HUN-GRR smiled again as he crossed his arms over his chest, "You see,
this little section of forest belongs to the Terrorcons!"

(TAG)

- Preston
